The paper deals with the bisimilarity problem for pushdown systems, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. This makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) the most likely category, as it deals with formal methods and their applications in computer science. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category, as pushdown systems are often used in programming language theory. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another likely category, as it directly relates to the topic of the paper. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LT (Computational Linguistics and Natural Language Processing) are less likely categories, but still possible as they deal with topics related to formal languages and automata theory.
